GET YOUR QUARTERS READY
The Martinsville PTO is having a Quarter Auction!
Where: Martinsville Elementary School Gym
When: March 7th
Time: 10:00am ‚Äì doors open at 9:00am
Paddles are $5.00 each

There will be many wonderful items to bid on, a 50/50 raffle, and the classrooms have prepared baskets for a silent auction!

We will also have pork sandwiches, chips, water, and baked treats.

Come out and support the Martinsville PTO and enjoy a fun morning with the chance to win great prizes!!

We are also accepting donations. Anything would be greatly appreciated. You can message this page, or contact Jordan Maxwell for questions. You can also drop donations off at the Elem. School.

Thank you for your continued support. We hope to see you there!

Kindergarten - 4th grade parents .
If you signed up to help at Field Day this Thursday, i will send you a form of communication Tues or Wed to confirm you can still help.
If you did not sign up, you will not be able to stay and help. The reason we have parents sign up, is so we can keep track of who is at the school helping , for the safety of the kiddos!
We appreciate everyone who is willing to help out. This day takes a lot of work, so all the help is wonderful.
Please sign in in the office and get your Field Day name tag Thursday at 12!

Also - pray for no rain üòÇ

- Jordan

post_text: Don't forget the PTO sponsored STEM Night will be from 5:00 - 6:30 this Thursday (tonight) in the Elementary gym. You can bring your kids and do fun science experiments in the gym. Walnut Prairie Wildlife will be there with animals, Marathon Oil will be bringing a farm/tank display, Chris Bkankenbaker will be showing us all about electricity, Mr. Penrod will demonstrate the 3D printer, and Mrs. Williams will be showing the latest technology she learned this summer. The night will be filled with lots of fun! You don't want to miss it!

The night will be filled with lots of fun! You don't want to miss it!

post_text:
Don't forget about the food drive next week!

The PTO will sponsor a Food Drive at the Elementary School March 6th-10th. Students can earn points based on items that they bring in. Any item on the Backpack Blessing Care package Program list will be accepted. The following items are worth more points. The class with the most points will receive a üç©Donut Party üç© from Sadies!

5 points - Individual soups

4 points - Juice boxes

3 points - Individual Mac and Cheese

2 points - Pudding cups

All other items worth 1 point - Breakfast bars, cereal bowls (individual or small size boxes), granola bar, fruit and grain bars, slim Jim's, Ramen Noodles, baked crackers(all individual packets), individual Goldfish packets, individual animal crackers, small individual raisin boxes, dried fruits, (individual boxes or packets), individual Jell-O cups, individual applesauce, individual cracker/cheese product, individual Rice Krispy treats, and individual ravioli cups.

**nothing with nuts please **all items need to be non-perishables
